1. FREE TRIAL

   Sentinel Backup may be used free of charge for a trial period of seven
   (7) calendar days from first run, with all features fully available.

2. SUBSCRIPTION REQUIRED AFTER THE TRIAL

   After the trial period, creating new backups (the `run` and `watch`
   commands, and the corresponding GUI actions) requires an active paid
   subscription from Wolf-Pak Innovations. Verifying, restoring, and
   checking the status of backups already created remain available at all
   times regardless of subscription status - a lapsed subscription never
   blocks access to your own previously-encrypted data.

   Subscriptions are billed monthly or annually under the Personal or
   Business plan. See the current pricing page or contact
   wolfpak_innovations@outlook.com. A one-time perpetual Personal license
   is also available on request.

3. LICENSE GRANT

   Subject to an active trial or paid subscription in good standing,
   Wolf-Pak Innovations grants you a non-exclusive, non-transferable
   license to install and use Sentinel Backup on the number of machines
   covered by your plan. You may not resell, sublicense, or redistribute
   the software, and you may not circumvent or attempt to circumvent the
   trial/license enforcement mechanism.

4. YOUR DATA

   Sentinel Backup encrypts your files locally before they reach any
   destination and never transmits your data to Wolf-Pak Innovations.
   Your backups, and the encryption keys that protect them, are yours
   alone - Wolf-Pak Innovations cannot access, recover, or decrypt them on
   your behalf, including if you lose your key.

